  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Fourway Engineering Pte Ltd</strong> is an ISO certified company which <strong>specialized in the design and manufacturing of Electrical Switchboard, Smart Panel, ACMV Panel, LCP and all types of customized empty metal enclosures.</strong></p><p>We are looking for an <strong>experienced Project Executive</strong> to join our team.</p><p><br /><u><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></u></p><ol><li>Manage all project activities from commencement to completion of projects according to scheduled datelines.</li><li>Provide support on schedule planning, quality control, costing and all documentations for projects and maintenance contracts.</li><li>Attend site meetings for all work in progress matters, safety and technical issues when required.</li><li>Liaise with Clients and Consultants.</li><li>To provide on-site technical support and directions to customers.</li><li>Liaising with customers pertaining on modification works and deadlines, including arrangement of appointments to take measurements, if deemed necessary.</li><li>Track and measure all project activities and provide weekly reports for review of progress.</li><li>Review initial project technical plans submitted by customer, action and risk containment plans to contain out-of-line situations.</li><li>All foul and undesirable deals and transactions must be avoided and reported to the management without hesitation.</li><li>Maintain proper documentation and reports for ease of retrieval of quality records and archived accordingly to the ISO 9001 requirement.</li><li>Any other ad-hoc duties as assigned.</li></ol><p><br /></p><p><u><strong>Job Requirements</strong></u></p><ul><li>Minimum 3 years of relevant working experience as a Project Executive.</li><li>Good knowledge of computer software like Microsoft Word and Excel is essential.</li><li>Good interpersonal, communication and negotiation skills.</li><li>Meticulous, responsible, able to multi-task and meet tight deadlines.</li><li>Self-driven, independent and a team-player.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Interested applicants</strong> are invited to submit a detailed resume, including:</p><ul><li>Current and expected salary</li><li>Earliest availability</li></ul>",
